misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that sorting the scores array in ascending order while swapping the corresponding names in lockstep will keep name-score pairs aligned, and that the top student will then be at index N-1.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap detected: this matches Java’s execution model and the intended parallel-array approach. The nested loops implement a valid bubble sort; the paired swaps maintain alignment between arrays; selecting names[N-1]/scores[N-1] after an ascending sort correctly yields the maximum.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None for valid inputs (N >= 1 and correct counts of names/scores). Produces correct output for the sample run and general cases.
